    stem: "A 55-year-old man with alcoholic liver cirrhosis presents to the emergency department vomiting bright red blood. He is haemodynamically unstable with BP 85/55 mmHg and HR 125 bpm. Following resuscitation with IV fluids and blood transfusion, upper endoscopy reveals grade III oesophageal varices with active oozing from one varix. Variceal band ligation (VBL) is performed successfully. Which of the following medications should be commenced immediately upon diagnosis and continued for 5 days?",
